x4freetext: The measurements were performed switching on
and off the beam polarization every 5 s.
at 32.5 degr. was used for
monitoring the beam vector polarization during the
vector analyzing power measurements.
The beam polarization monitor
consisted of a gas cell of 7 cm diam., filled with 3He
gas at 0.5 bar pressure.
Protons were detected in a CsI scintillation counter.
The error bars for the analyzing power
measurements contain besides the statistical errors
also those connected with the setting of the angle
alpha by means of the Wien filter
